7 Reporting issues
******************

To report build or installation problems, include:
  1. the compiler name and version (e.g.  'gcc' version 10),
  2. the C standard library name and version (e.g.  'glibc' version
     2.x),
  3. the output of the 'configure' script.  You can capture it by
     running './configure > configure-output.txt 2>&1',
  4. the generated 'config.log' file,
  5. the generated 'config.h' file, if it exists,
  6. the output of the 'make' command.  You can capture it by running
     'make > make-output.txt 2>&1',
  7. any other error messages,
  8. any other information that you think could lead to solving the
     problem.

   To report usage problems, include:
  1. all the above things you include when reporting building problems,
  2. a description of the problem that the software causes,
  3. any error messages that are displayed,
  4. information whether you tried other wiping methods and whether they
     work,
  5. information whether you tried wiping just parts (undelete data,
     free space, partial blocks) of the filesystem and whether it
     worked,
  6. information whether you tried another filesystems, if possible, and
     whether it worked,
  7. (if the problem is with a filesystem) if possible, the whole input
     filesystem or a minimalistic input file that causes the problem to
     show (e.g.  file of zero length or with a strange name),
  8. any other information that you think could lead to solving the
     problem.


